This paper focuses on analyzing human brain activity using fMRI data through signal processing and dimensionality analysis. The use of Independent Component Analysis (ICA) and fractal analysis suggests a focus on machine learning and neural networks (cs.NE) and statistical learning (cs.LG). The study also involves visual and visuo-motor tasks, which suggests a potential focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the investigation of cognitive tasks and brain activity suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
